# Foreword to the 2nd edition (2025)

[M]{custom-style=initial-joined}[ost of what I wrote]{.smallcaps}, in the foreword to the first edition of this book in 2024, still holds true.

I have contributed a few more fixes and improvements to SILE's math engine. This book has been updated accordingly, with new examples --- particularly for primes, stretched delimiters, and accents.

There is still room for improvement, and using the system remains one of the best ways to uncover edge cases.
After all, most issues have been found simply by throwing equations at it.
That said, contributions have been quiet lately.
A more active exchange would help shape the math engine into something truly robust and broadly useful.

