What I find interesting about SILE's approach to math is that it offers an independent implementation of both MathML (without relying on a web stack) and TeX-like math (without using a traditional TeX engine).
There aren't many free and open-source typesetting systems that handle math well.
Rather than competing, these projects have a real opportunity to learn from one another and collectively advance the tools available to the community.
